NOTE ON DISTRIBUTION: the open dataset skews toward number-properties / percent /
word-problem items, and leaves several leaves empty (fractions, decimals, linear
equations, absolute value, functions, sequences, expressions). The AUTHORED seed
set is intentionally designed to cover ALL 18 leaves so the deck has guaranteed,
balanced, verified coverage regardless of what scraping yields.


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5. LICENSING & LEGAL (honest, per PRD Sections 13 & 19)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- We NEVER claim a license we cannot verify.
- seed.json .......... "authored-gmatwiz". Original questions written for
                       GMATWiz; safe to redistribute under the project license.
- questions.json ..... "Apache-2.0" for every item (all from AQuA-RAT, whose
                       repository is Apache-2.0). Redistributable WITH attribution
                       (see the citation above and each item's "source" field).
- Forum / user content (GMAT Club, Reddit) would be tagged "scraped-unverified",
  treated as copyright-retained, QUARANTINED, and kept OUT of any redistributable
  pool and OUT of the learning pool's "official-question protection" path. None
  was ingested in this run (both were blocked and respected).
- Official/copyrighted GMAT items are never relabeled as open and never enter the
  learning pool (PRD Section 13 guardrail).


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6. HOW TO REPRODUCE
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Requirements: Python 3 standard library only (no pip installs needed). If the
optional "requests" package is present it is used automatically; otherwise urllib.

  # Re-author + verify the seed set (offline, deterministic):
  python3 make_seed.py

  # Run the scraper across all sources (needs network for the open dataset):
  python3 scraper.py

  # Useful flags:
  python3 scraper.py --sources aqua_rat          # only the open dataset
  python3 scraper.py --limit 100                 # cap kept items per source
  python3 scraper.py --delay 2.0                 # politeness delay (seconds)
  python3 scraper.py --ignore-robots aqua_rat    # bypass robots ONLY for the
                                                 # named open/own source(s)
  python3 taxonomy.py                            # quick tagger self-check

Outputs are written next to the scripts (questions.json, scrape_report.json,
seed.json, raw/). Re-running is safe and idempotent (stable content-hash ids;
raw captures are timestamped).


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7. PIPELINE DETAILS
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- robots.txt: checked per host via urllib.robotparser, cached; a 401/403 on
  robots.txt is treated conservatively as Disallow. Override only via
  --ignore-robots for clearly-open or self-owned sources.
- Normalization: trims/normalizes whitespace; requires exactly 5 distinct,
  non-empty A-E options and a valid correct letter; drops geometry and Data
  Sufficiency items (PRD scope); auto-tags the topic; assigns difficulty.
- Topic tagging: weighted keyword scoring over stem + options, with a specificity
  tie-break (taxonomy.py). Unclassifiable items default to number_properties.
- Dedup: exact content hash + near-duplicate detection via token-set Jaccard
  similarity (default threshold 0.85) across all sources combined.
- Seed verification: each authored item ships a check() that recomputes the
  answer from first principles, finds the matching option, and asserts it equals
  the labelled "correct". 42/42 verified in this build.


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8. KNOWN LIMITATIONS
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Scraped content is provided AS-IS under its source license; correctness is NOT
  independently guaranteed (AQuA-RAT is real but mildly noisy: a few rationales/
  answers can be imperfect). It is bulk volume, clearly flagged by source +
  license. The AUTHORED seed set is the clean, verified core.
- Two sources (GMAT Club, Reddit) are blocked for compliant offline scraping.
  Compliant paths exist but require accounts/keys: GMAT Club partner access, or
  the official Reddit Data API (OAuth). These can be added as new adapters
  later without changing the schema.
- The difficulty heuristic for scraped items is approximate (the dataset has no
  difficulty labels).
